div1.p: United States District Court Western District of Washington Northern Division
In the Matter of the Application of Chin Hing for a Writ of Habeas Corpus } No.2857 Stipulation.
It is hereby stipulated and agreed between counsel for the petitioner and respondent in the above entitled cause, that the hearing in said cause may be continued until April 26th, 1915.
div1.ab: John J Sullivan Attorney for Petitioner
Clay Allen GP Fishburne Attorneys for Respondent
div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington
In the Matter of the Application of Chin Hing for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Filed in the U.S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington Northern Division APR 12 1915 Frank L. Crosby, Clerk, By EML Deputy 2x
